observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a.	Designate new members of the Inventory Committee with less crucial functions to focus more on the conduct of one-time cleansing of PPE accounts without hampering the daily operations of the Municipality;

b.	Enforce active involvement of the members of the Inventory Committee to conduct one-time cleansing of PPE accounts in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006;

c.	Require the members of the Inventory Committee to observe and exhaust all other the necessary procedures provided in the COA Circular No. 2020-006 to come up with a reliable PPE balances that are verifiable as to their existence, condition and accountability.

We recommended to the Municipal Mayor the following courses of action:

a.)	Require the Municipal Accountant to return the unutilized balance of ₱44,530.00 to the DOST Regional Office No. VIII;

b.)	Ensure that all funds received from National Government Agencies (NGAs) are utilized in accordance with the provisions in the Memoranda of Agreement entered into between the Municipality and the NGAs.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a.direct the Inventory Committee to complete the physical inventory-taking, and conduct the same annually, in order to prepare a reliable RPCPPE and present the accurate PPE account balances;

b.require the Municipal Accountant and General Service Officer to maintain/update and reconcile the balances of their respective property records.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require the:

a.	Municipal Health Officer to coordinate with the General Services Officer when there are transfers or donations in-kind which are directly delivered to the Rural Health Unit;

b.	General Services Officer to acknowledge receipt of the transferred vaccines and other medical supplies from the Provincial Health Office to the Rural Health Unit and prepare the necessary documents to be submitted to the Municipal Accountant;

c.	Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary journal entries; and

d.	Municipal Health Officer and other concerned officials to provide measures to efficiently use the COVID-19 vaccines and other donated items from other government agencies to prevent expiration and wastage.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor take the following courses of actions:

1.)	establish close coordination with the GFPS and the implementing offices in GAD planning and monitoring to ascertain the achievement of objectives and targets of the GAD PPAs;

2.)	capacitate the Executive Committee and Technical Working Group of the GFPS, including the heads of the implementing offices on gender analysis trainings to ensure the gender-responsiveness of GAD-attributed PPAs.

We recommended the Local Chief Executive to require the Municipal Treasurer to:
1. Monitor the remittances of all collecting officers and require them to remit all collections daily and intact or as soon as the collection reach P10,000.00 to safeguard the government funds to possible loss or misuse;
2. Provide details on the deposited amount as to the particular collections of the collecting officer; and tracing of which collections were deposited;
3. Refrain from remitting/ reporting the prior year collections in the current year so that collections and income shall be properly accounted for.
